libXcolor:

    The libXcolor library is a reference implementation of the net-color spec.
    It allows to attach colour regions to X windows to communicate with colour
    servers.


Internet:
    sources: git clone git://www.oyranos.org/git/xcolor
    www:     OpenICC http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/OpenIcc
    email:   http://lists.freedesktop.org/mailman/listinfo/openicc


Dependencies:
    Xorg www.x.org


Building:
    $ make
    $ make install


